# .raw-exemptions/raw_8.list — grandfather list for raw#8 (stage/phase token retire)
# format: <file_path> | <line_range> | <reason> | <expiry YYYY-MM-DD>
# expiry REQUIRED — indefinite grandfather forbidden.
#
# raw#8 (project_raw8_stage_token_retire) bans hardcoded stage0/stage1
# tokens in ACTIVE code paths — interp/dispatch is the SSOT. Historical
# tools that pin to a specific stage/phase as their RESEARCH SUBJECT
# (i.e. the phase IS the artifact, not a missing-dispatch shortcut)
# are jurisdiction-out: research.
#
# 2026-04-26 anima seed entries — same files as raw_7.list F2 group;
# carried separately here so raw#8 enforcement can list them without
# coupling F2 (filename-shape) and raw#8 (token-in-code) semantics.

# Phase-pinned smoke + sweep runners — the phase number IS the research
# subject (p1 smoke vs p4 sweep), not a stale dispatch fallback.
tool/phi_extractor_p1_smoke.hexa | * | phi-extractor p1 smoke runner — phase IS the research subject, not a missing-dispatch shortcut [jurisdiction-out: research] — owner: anima | 2027-04-26
tool/p4_sweep_runner.hexa        | * | p4 sweep runner — phase IS the research subject, not a missing-dispatch shortcut [jurisdiction-out: research] — owner: anima | 2027-04-26
